<TEXT>
<P>
 It's hot. It's smoky. And there's definite fire danger if you have a tender 
palate.Garden of Eatin's new smoky chipotle organic red bean dip boosts its 
fire power with a double dose of jalapenos -- fresh ones and the dried smoked 
jalapenos known as chipotle chiles. The large, red, organically grown beans are 
left whole, which makes this dip seem a little like incendiary chili beans. It 
sells for $3.29 in natural foods stores. BARBARA HANSEN 
