<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSINESS / BRIEFLY; MET MUSEUM SHOP OPENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Metropolitan Museum of Art opened a shop in Old Pasadena on Sunday. It is 
the third such shop to open in the Los Angeles area, and the 14th in the 
country. 
</P>
<P>
 The store, at the One Colorado shopping plaza, features reproductions from the 
museum's collection, including cards, calendars, stationery, jewelry, scarves, 
books, glass and silver. 
</P>
<P>
 The store will have a more extensive print and poster collection than the 
museum's other shops, and will change themes monthly to correspond with museum 
exhibits. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 More than 2,000 dripping customers took the plunge last month at the opening 
of Raging Waters' newest water slide, the four-story Vortex. 
</P>
<P>
 The ride hurls visitors at 20 m.p.h. down 270-foot plumes flooded by fog, 
wind, pulsating lights and electrical storm-like sound effects. The Vortex took 
120 days to build and cost about $500,000. 
</P>
