<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: WALNUT; LIBRARY HOURS CUT TO 2-DAY SCHEDULE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Walnut Library will reduce its hours beginning Friday, opening only on 
Tuesdays and Thursdays from 1 to 8 p.m. The library previously was open five 
days a week, but continuing budget crunches in the county library system forced 
some new cutbacks. 
</P>
<P>
 The reduction will save the financially troubled county library system about 
$171,000 over the next year. 
</P>
<P>
 The book drop in the parking lot will remain open 24 hours a day. On the days 
when the Walnut Library is closed, library employees suggest that patrons use 
the libraries in Rowland Heights and Diamond Bar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
