<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MONTEREY PARK; NEW U.S. CITIZENS TO BE HONORED JULY 4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city's Fourth of July celebration at Barnes Memorial Park will include a 
ceremony to honor Monterey Park residents who became U.S. citizens in the past 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 The city will give special-recognition certificates to all city residents who 
became or will become citizens between July 1, 1993, and this Monday. Those 
eligible for a certificate should call the Parks and Recreation Department at 
(818) 307-1389 or Councilwoman Marie Purvis at (818) 280-9025. 
</P>
<P>
 Fourth of July celebrations start at 1 p.m. and include stage entertainment 
and food at the park, 400 S. McPherrin Ave. There will be fireworks at 9 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
