<HEADLINE>
<P>
WILLIAM A. HENRY III; PULITZER-WINNING DRAMA CRITIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 William A. Henry III, 44, Pulitzer Prize-winning drama critic for Time 
magazine. Henry, who joined the newsmagazine in 1981, a year after he won the 
coveted prize in 1980 for his television criticism for the Boston Globe.As a 
Globe reporter, he also contributed to the reporting and writing that won the 
public service Pulitzer for the Globe in 1975. He also worked briefly as a 
critic and columnist for the New York Daily News and wrote several books, 
including a biography of Jackie Gleason. His final book, "In Defense of 
Elitism," is scheduled for publication in September. A native of South Orange, 
N.J., Henry was educated at Yale where he was executive editor of both the 
student newspaper and the yearbook. On Tuesday in London of a heart attack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
