<P>
 Belgium's French-language daily, Le Soir, published today a small story 
written by player Georges Grun on his impressions of the trip from Orlando to 
Washington: "We are heading toward Washington. Everything is made so that it 
happens as quick as possible.Traveling in such conditions is quite pleasant. 
Furthermore, a telephone is available on the back of our seat in the airplane, 
usable by credit card. It is always reassuring to know you can call somebody in 
case the plane crashes. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 "Georgetown resembles more what we are used to seeing at home: numerous nice 
cafes and restaurants, fashionable boutiques open until late at night, a few 
antiques shops. 
</P>
<P>
 "This morning we had a walk in the parks. It is incredible to see the number 
of people who run. (Americans) work out, drink Diet Coke, but in general they 
are all fat, and without complexes; show me your fat, and I'll show you my 
cellulite! In the land of the hamburger, the Big Mac is king." ISABELLE 
MAELCAMP Times Brussels bureau 
</P>
