<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-LAGUNA OFFICIAL IS NEW AVALON MANAGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert Clark, who worked for the city of Laguna Beach for 13 years, took over 
as Avalon city manager this week. 
</P>
<P>
 Clark worked for the Parks and Recreation Department and held positions as 
assistant to the city manager and deputy city manager in Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 He will live on Catalina with his wife Judy, a Long Beach psychologist, and 
their three children. 
</P>
<P>
 Clark replaces Chuck Prince, who resigned in January after five years in the 
job, Assistant City Manager Peter Woolson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Clark was chosen from six finalists, Woolson said. 
</P>
