<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMPARING THE POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CECILIA RASMUSSEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles police officers have been trying to win a raise from city 
officials since their contract ran out almost two years ago. Here is a look at 
how LAPD compares to some of the nation's largest police departments. A. SAN 
FRANCISCO Population: 730,000Total full-time officers: 1,817Patrolman pay: 
$43,952 to $51,574 Homicides: 17.8 per 100,000 Average years on force: N/A B. 
LOS ANGELES Population: 3,485,398 Full-time officers: 7,600 Patrolman pay: 
$33,157 to $44,537 Homicides: 30.2 per 100,000 Average years on force: N/A C. 
SAN DIEGO Population: 1,110,549Total full-time officers: 1,885Patrolman pay: 
