<P>
 Seattle 9, Detroit 4 -- Jay Buhner's home run ignited a five-run rally in the 
seventh inning that carried the Mariners to victory at Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
 Edgar Martinez went 4 for 4 with a homer, two runs scored and two RBIs for the 
Mariners. 
</P>
<P>
 With the score tied 3-3, Buhner led off with his 15th homer against Storm 
Davis (0-2) to put the Mariners ahead for good. Luis Sojo hit a run-scoring 
single, Dan Wilson had a two-run double and Martinez capped the inning with an 
RBI single. 
