<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; RIVERSIDE; MAN WITH AIDS GETS 38 YEARS IN GIRL'S RAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man charged with raping his wife's 7-year-old daughter at his wedding 
reception and passing on the virus that causes AIDS has been sentenced to 38 
years in prison. Frank C. Bridges, 43, pleaded guilty to felony rape, sexual 
penetration with a foreign object and three counts of forced lewd acts with a 
child.The charges included special allegations of inflicting great bodily 
injury and committing a sex offense while knowingly infected with AIDS. 
Bridges, a former county juvenile probation officer, was immediately sentenced 
by Riverside Superior Court Judge W. Charles Morgan. Bridges was accused of 
raping the child Jan. 15 in the Canyon Crest home where he had exchanged 
wedding vows with the victim's mother earlier in the day. The 37-year-old 
mother faces trial next month on charges of felony child endangerment and being 
an accessory after the fact. A month later, the child tested positive for the 
human immunodeficiency virus. The girl is living with relatives in the Midwest 
and has not been told she is HIV positive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
