<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN POURS GASOLINE ON SELF, STARTS FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 21-year-old man poured gasoline on himself at a gas station Wednesday and 
then ignited it, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, whose name was not released, walked to the Arco service station at 
2415 W. Lincoln Ave. about 2:15 p.m. and paid for $1 worth of gas. He placed 
everything from his pockets on top of a gas pump, pumped gasoline over his body 
and set it afire, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Someone put out the flames with a fire extinguisher, and the man was rushed to 
UC Irvine Medical Center, where he was in critical condition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
