ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; ROADS TO BE CLOSED FOR SIX MONTHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Skyline Drive, Ladera Vista Drive and the north tip of Acacia Avenue will be 
closed to the public for about six months beginning July 6. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction crews will be grading and realigning Skyline and Ladera Vista as 
part of the Unocal Corp.'s efforts to sell custom-home lots along those 
streets, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 In 1991, the City Council gave Unocal the nod to develop the 300-acre East 
Coyote Hills area. Development plans call for the realignment of the roads and 
a public 18-hole golf course just south of Bastanchury Road between Brea and 
State College boulevards. 
</P>
<P>
 The golf course and the realigned roads are scheduled to open in January, a 
Unocal official said. MIMI KO 
