ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; SCHOOL TRUSTEES NAME INTERIM SUPT. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Santa Ana Unified School District board has named Don Champlin as interim 
superintendent to replace Rudy M. Castruita, who will leave the district in 
mid-July. 
</P>
<P>
 The board made its decision in closed session at its Tuesday meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Champlin, who now serves as assistant superintendent of personnel services, 
will take over effective July 18, district spokeswoman Diane Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
 He has worked for the district since 1986 and will replace Castruita, who has 
accepted a job as superintendent of schools for San Diego County. Castruita 
joined the district in 1985, Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
 As interim superintendent of the county's largest school district, Champlin 
will oversee 3,600 full-time and 500 part-time employees. The district serves 
nearly 50,000 students. 
</P>
<P>
 A search firm was named last week to find a qualified candidate to take the 
$124,000-a-year job and district officials have said they expect the search to 
take about four months.JON NALICK 
</P>
