<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRVINE STORE WILL BE HONORED FOR WORK WITH DISABLED EMPLOYEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Irvine discount store will be honored today by the Orange County Employment 
Advocacy Network at a luncheon held to recognize employers who hire people with 
disabilities. 
</P>
<P>
 The Target store at 3750 Barranca Parkway will be named the most innovative 
employer of the year in Orange County for creating a position for a worker with 
a walking problem that included tasks he could accomplish despite his 
disability. 
</P>
<P>
 Store managers also modified the employee's hours so that he could take the 
bus to and from work, said Kathy Moore, coordinator of the luncheon. 
</P>
<P>
 Today's event will be hosted by KTLA-TV sportscaster Ed Arnold and will 
include a speech by Geri Jewell, an actress from the 1980s sitcom "Facts of 
Life." 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange County Employment Advocacy Network is a consortium of agencies that 
help disabled people find jobs and assist employers with special job training, 
Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to Target, three other Orange County businesses will be honored 
for their work with disabled employees. 
</P>
<P>
 The luncheon begins at 11 a.m. at the Anaheim Marriott, 700 Convention Way. 
For more information, call (714) 724-6730. 
</P>
