<HEADLINE>
<P>
THREE AREA GOLFERS ADVANCE IN PGA JUNIOR MATCH PLAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A trio of area players survived the first two rounds of head-to-head 
competition Thursday in the Southern California PGA junior match play 
championships at El Dorado Golf Course. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Farris of Newhall and Anthony Marciano of Simi Valley each advanced to 
today's round of 16. Farris defeated Jeff Bhaedhayajibh of Chino, 6 and 5, in 
an afternoon match while Marciano routed Ira Flood of Los Angeles, 8 and 6. 
</P>
<P>
 In the girls' competition, Linda Ishii of Westlake Village defeated Susan Kim 
of Cerritos, 4 and 3, in an afternoon quarterfinal. Ishii will face Natalie 
Wong of Montebello in the semifinals today. 
</P>
