July 12. The suit contends that an earlier vote approving the buyout was taken 
before union members had time to fully understand details of the plan and that 
"many provisions were not clearly explained." Some shareholders previously sued 
UAL seeking to stop the buyout. A hearing on that suit is set for Wednesday in 
Delaware. 
</P>
</TEXT>
