<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; WITH TWO GAMES LEFT, SECOND ROUND IS FAR 
FROM SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELLIOTT ALMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Because of the system used to determine first-, second- and third-place teams 
in World Cup group play, Romania must wait until today's final first-round 
games before learning who it will play Sunday at the Rose Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 As winner of Group A, Romania is expected to play Bulgaria or Italy in the 
second round, but there are a number of scenarios that could change 
everything.Italy finished third in Group E, but depending on tonight's matches, 
Argentina, Bulgaria or Nigeria could finish third in Group D. If the 
third-place team from Group D qualifies for the round of 16, Romania will play 
that team. If only two teams from Group D advance, Romania will play Italy. 
</P>
<P>
 Argentina, which leads Group D, will finish first and play Monday in Foxboro, 
Mass., if it defeats or ties Bulgaria tonight. Bulgaria would need at least a 
tie to advance to the second round as the third-place team. 
</P>
<P>
 But if Argentina loses by enough goals, and Nigeria defeats Greece by enough 
goals at Foxboro, the Argentines would finish third. Nigeria would finish third 
with a big loss, and, get this: Greece still could finish third if it were to 
win by, say, 9-0. 
</P>
<P>
 For Argentina, a close loss or tie might mean a second-round match against 
Italy. Otherwise, the Argentines are likely to play Belgium. ELLIOTT ALMOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
